timeline.bodyText:
There's not only org.junit.jupiter.api.Test that indicate it's a JUnit 5 test method, you can use UnitTestUtils.hasJUnit5TestAnnotation(...)
I recently use it in JunitNestedAnnotationCheck:
  private static boolean hasJUnit5TestMethods(ClassTree classTree) {
    return classTree.members().stream()
      .filter(member -> member.is(Tree.Kind.METHOD))
      .map(MethodTree.class::cast)
      .anyMatch(UnitTestUtils::hasJUnit5TestAnnotation);
  }

