we should add some test cases about CLASS like:
  public static class WithoutTest { // Compliant

  }

  public static class PublicWithOneTest { // Noncompliant
    @Test
    void test() {}
  }

  static class WithOneTest { // Compliant
    @Test
    void test() {}
  }

Usually, when the message is constant, we test it only once.
So, here it's ok, you can use // Noncompliant [[sc=3;ec=9]] {{Remove this access modifier}}
And elsewhere it's enough to use // Noncompliant, without the location and the message

